	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=31354"><span id="Scholar">Yunna</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">19 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm not exactly sure what the deal with Ogres is, but here's a couple of facts I do know.<br/><br/>At level 60 a warrior gets 6 HP / 1 STA.&nbsp;&nbsp;For example if I put on a 5 STA ring, my HPs go up by 30 HP.  This is true for ALL level 60 warriors, regardless of race.  For warriors this number of HP/STA goes up about every 10 levels by 1.  Starting at lev 1-10 with 1 sta = 1hp, etc etc.<br/><br/>Other races scale down from there.  Pure casters have somewhere around 3 HP/STA at lev 60, priests a bit more, hybrids more, etc.<br/><br/>As a lev 60 wood elven warioress that started with a fairly low STA (I was created during the time when it was told STR was best stat to put points in - doh!) I have 5804 HP with raid buffs.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Yunna</td></tr>
